The issue is deeper — `_get_or_add_definition()` itself is broken in your version of python-docx. We need to bypass it entirely and manipulate the XML directly through the document's part relationships.

Try this replacement for `update_header`:

```python
def update_header(self, model_id, model_name):
    from docx.oxml.ns import qn, nsmap
    from docx.oxml import OxmlElement
    from lxml import etree

    new_text = f"{model_id} {model_name} - Validation Report"

    for section in self.doc.sections:
        # Access the sectPr element directly
        sectPr = section._sectPr

        # Remove existing header references
        for hdrRef in sectPr.findall(qn('w:headerReference')):
            sectPr.remove(hdrRef)

        # Create a new header part manually
        from docx.opc.part import Part
        from docx.opc.packuri import PackURI
        from docx.oxml import parse_xml

        header_xml = (
            '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>'
            '<w:hdr xmlns:wpc="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingCanvas" '
            'xmlns:w="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/wordprocessingml/2006/main">'
            '<w:p><w:pPr>'
            '<w:jc w:val="center"/>'
            '<w:pBdr><w:bottom w:val="single" w:sz="12" w:space="1" w:color="000000"/></w:pBdr>'
            '</w:pPr>'
            f'<w:r><w:t>{new_text}</w:t></w:r>'
            '</w:p>'
            '</w:hdr>'
        )

        header_part = Part(
            PackURI('/word/header1.xml'),
            'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.header+xml',
            header_xml.encode('utf-8'),
            self.doc.part.package
        )

        rId = self.doc.part.relate_to(
            header_part,
            'http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/relationships/header'
        )

        # Add headerReference to sectPr
        hdrRef = OxmlElement('w:headerReference')
        hdrRef.set(qn('w:type'), 'default')
        hdrRef.set(qn('r:id'), rId)
        sectPr.append(hdrRef)
```

If you're still hitting issues, the most reliable fix is to **downgrade python-docx**:

```bash
pip install "python-docx==0.8.11"
```

Then revert to your original code — version 0.8.11 has the stable `section.header` API that your original code was written for. The newer versions (1.x+) broke backward compatibility on header/footer access.
